{"name": "sheets_server_sheets", "description": "Spreadsheet operations: create, read, edit .xlsx and CSV files.

Use action='help' to list all operations and parameters.
Paths start with '/' and are relative to workspace root (APP_FS_ROOT).", "parameters": {"additionalProperties": false, "properties": {"request": {"description": "Input for sheets meta-tool.", "properties": {"action": {"description": "Action to perform", "enum": ["help", "create", "delete", "read_tab", "read_csv", "list_tabs", "add_tab", "delete_tab", "edit", "add_content", "delete_content", "create_chart", "filter_tab"], "type": "string"}, "file_path": {"description": "(Optional) Path to file within workspace. File extension depends on the action: '.xlsx' for most actions (e.g., '/report.xlsx'), '.csv' for 'read_csv' action (e.g., '/data/sales.csv'). REQUIRED for all actions except 'create'. Paths always start with '/' which represents your workspace root folder (not system root). Example: If workspace is /Users/me/project, then '/report.xlsx' accesses /Users/me/project/report.xlsx", "nullable": true, "type": "string"}, "directory": {"description": "(Optional) Folder path within workspace where file will be created (e.g., '/' for root, '/data' for data subfolder). REQUIRED for 'create' action only. Use with file_name to specify the complete path.", "nullable": true, "type": "string"}, "file_name": {"description": "(Optional) File name with .xlsx extension. REQUIRED for 'create' action (e.g., 'report.xlsx').", "nullable": true, "type": "string"}, "tab_index": {"description": "(Optional) 0-based tab position (0=first tab, 1=second tab, etc.). REQUIRED for: read_tab, filter_tab, delete_tab, add_content, delete_content. Cannot delete the last remaining tab in the spreadsheet. To find tab index: Use 'list_tabs' action first to see all tabs and their indices.", "nullable": true, "type": "integer"}, "tab_name": {"description": "(Optional) Name for new tab. REQUIRED for 'add_tab' action only. Maximum 31 characters. Cannot contain: \ / ? * [ ]. Must not already exist in workbook. For reading/editing existing tabs, use tab_index instead (see list_tabs to find indices).", "nullable": true, "type": "string"}, "cell_range": {"description": "(Optional) Cell range for 'read_tab' and 'filter_tab' (e.g., 'A1:C5'). For filter_tab, must be a range (e.g., 'A1:D100'), not a single cell", "nullable": true, "type": "string"}, "include_formulas": {"description": "(Optional) Include formula information for 'read_tab'. Default: False. Why: Formulas require dual-pass loading (slower).", "nullable": true, "type": "boolean"}, "max_rows": {"description": "(Optional) Maximum rows to return for 'read_tab'. Default: 1000. Why: Prevents excessive token usage. Set None for unlimited.", "nullable": true, "type": "integer"}, "max_cols": {"description": "(Optional) Maximum columns to return for 'read_tab'. Default: 100. Why: Prevents excessive token usage. Set None for unlimited.", "nullable": true, "type": "integer"}, "compact": {"description": "(Optional) Use compact CSV-style output for read operations. Default: False. Why: Table format is easier to read but uses more tokens.", "nullable": true, "type": "boolean"}, "include_diagnostics": {"description": "(Optional) Include diagnostic info for 'filter_tab' when no matches. Default: False. Why: Reduces token usage when not debugging.", "nullable": true, "type": "boolean"}, "sheets": {"description": "(Optional) Sheet definitions for 'create'. REQUIRED for create. Format: [{'name': 'Sheet1', 'headers': ['A','B'], 'rows': [[1,2], [3,4]]}]. Row lengths must match header count if headers provided. Sheet names must be unique.", "items": {"properties": {}, "type": "object"}, "nullable": true, "type": "array"}, "sheet_data": {"description": "(Optional) Data for add_tab action: {'headers': [...], 'rows': [[...], [...]]}. Row lengths must match header count if headers provided. Headers freeze the first row automatically.", "nullable": true, "properties": {}, "type": "object"}, "operations": {"description": "(Optional) Operations for 'edit' action. Each operation is a dictionary with 'type' field.

Valid operation types: 'set_cell', 'append_rows', 'rename_sheet', 'format_cells', 'merge_cells', 'unmerge_cells', 'set_column_width', 'set_row_height', 'freeze_panes', 'add_named_range', 'delete_named_range', 'add_data_validation', 'add_conditional_formatting', 'set_auto_filter', 'set_number_format', 'add_image'.

Examples:
- {'type': 'set_cell', 'sheet': 'Sheet1', 'cell': 'A1', 'value': 123}
- {'type': 'append_rows', 'sheet': 'Sheet1', 'rows': [[1, 2], [3, 4]]}
- {'type': 'rename_sheet', 'sheet': 'Sheet1', 'new_name': 'Data'}
- {'type': 'format_cells', 'sheet': 'Sheet1', 'range': 'A1:B2', 'font_bold': True}

All operations are applied in order. If any operation fails, entire edit action fails. Use sheets_schema tool for the complete list of supported operations and their parameters.", "items": {"properties": {}, "type": "object"}, "nullable": true, "type": "array"}, "cell": {"description": "(Optional) Cell reference for add_content/delete_content (e.g., 'A1'). For 'add_content' action, the target cell must be empty; this tool will not overwrite existing values.", "nullable": true, "type": "string"}, "value": {"description": "(Optional) Value parameter for specific actions:
- add_content: Value to write to cell (string, number, boolean, or None)
- Filters: Not used directly here - use 'filters' parameter instead with condition values
Not used by other actions.", "nullable": true, "type": "string"}, "sheet": {"description": "(Optional) Worksheet tab name (e.g., 'Sheet1', 'Sales Data'). For 'create_chart': the sheet containing chart source data (must exist). For other actions: target sheet.", "nullable": true, "type": "string"}, "data_range": {"description": "(Optional) Cell range containing chart data in A1:Z99 notation (e.g., 'A1:C10', 'B2:E20'). Must be a bounded rectangular range. Requires at least 2 rows if include_header=True. First column typically contains category labels, other columns contain data series", "nullable": true, "type": "string"}, "chart_type": {"description": "(Optional) Type of chart to create. Valid values: 'bar' (vertical bar/column chart, default), 'line' (line chart), 'pie' (pie chart)", "enum": ["bar", "line", "pie"], "nullable": true, "type": "string"}, "title": {"description": "(Optional) Chart title (for create_chart action)", "nullable": true, "type": "string"}, "position": {"description": "(Optional) Cell reference for top-left corner of the chart (e.g., 'E2', 'G5'). Default is 'E2'. Chart is placed in the same sheet as the source data", "nullable": true, "type": "string"}, "categories_column": {"description": "(Optional) 1-based column index within data_range for X-axis category labels. Default (null) uses first column as categories. Set to 0 to skip categories entirely. For pie charts, this determines slice labels", "nullable": true, "type": "integer"}, "include_header": {"description": "(Optional) If true (default), first row of data_range is treated as series names/labels. If false, all rows are data. When true, data_range must contain at least 2 rows", "nullable": true, "type": "boolean"}, "delimiter": {"description": "(Optional) CSV column delimiter character. Default: ','. Examples: '\t' for tab-delimited (TSV), '|' for pipe-delimited, ';' for semicolon-separated", "nullable": true, "type": "string"}, "encoding": {"description": "(Optional) CSV file character encoding. Default: 'utf-8'. Other options: 'utf-8-sig' (UTF-8 with BOM), 'latin-1', 'cp1252', 'ascii'", "nullable": true, "type": "string"}, "has_header": {"description": "(Optional) CSV has header row (default: True)", "nullable": true, "type": "boolean"}, "row_limit": {"description": "(Optional) Maximum data rows to return from CSV (default 1000, None for unlimited). Header row does NOT count toward this limit. Examples: has_header=True + row_limit=100 returns 101 rows total (1 header + 100 data). has_header=False + row_limit=100 returns 100 rows total.", "nullable": true, "type": "integer"}, "filters": {"description": "(Optional) Filter conditions for 'filter_tab'. Each: {column: 'A' or header name, operator: string, value: ...}. Column resolution: When use_headers=True, header names are checked FIRST before column letters. cell_range must be a range (e.g., 'A1:B10'), not a single cell. Valid operators: 'equals', 'not_equals', 'greater_than', 'less_than', 'greater_than_or_equal', 'less_than_or_equal', 'contains', 'not_contains', 'starts_with', 'ends_with', 'is_empty', 'is_not_empty'. The 'is_empty' and 'is_not_empty' operators do not require a value parameter.", "items": {"properties": {}, "type": "object"}, "nullable": true, "type": "array"}, "match_all": {"description": "(Optional) For 'filter_tab': if True (default), all conditions must match (AND); if False, any match (OR)", "nullable": true, "type": "boolean"}, "use_headers": {"description": "(Optional) For 'filter_tab': if True (default), first row is headers and column names can reference them", "nullable": true, "type": "boolean"}}, "required": ["action"], "type": "object"}}, "required": ["request"], "type": "object"}}
